edu.mit.jwi.content
Interface IParserProvider

All Known Implementing Classes:
ParserProvider
public interface IParserProvider

Objects that implement this interface provide objects of type ILineParser for specified content types. IDictionary objects can use instances of this interface to automatically determine which parsers to use for what data resources.

Since:
1.5.0
Version:
1.00, 04/15/06
Author:
Mark A. Finlayson

registerParser

ILineParser registerParser(IContentType contentType,
                           ILineParser parser)
Registers a parser under the specified content type. If this registration replaces a previous parser, that one is returned.

registerParser

Registers a parser under the specified data type. If this registration replaces a previous parser, that one is returned.
